In this episode of So This Happened, we reviewed the ongoing land dispute at Magodo. Residents of Magodo phase 2  estate in Lagos State have called on the governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu to intervene and stop the planned demolition of properties in the estate. In another matter, relating to the Lagos State Government, five students and staff of Dowen College linked to the death of Sylvester Oromoni, a student of the school, have been cleared of any wrongdoing by the government. Lastly, just when the world is still battling the highly-infectious Omicron strain of Covid, a new variant, IHU, has been discovered in France. This IHU has so far infected 12 people living in southeastern France.